		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>

<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Look at Kaldiin (cleric), for example. A few druids praised him for posting constructively, but didn't notice how backhanded his comments were. He started off by saying "grats druids", then proceeded to make three statements which basically said druids could already heal just fine&nbsp;in high level zones.... then wrapped it up with a snide remark implying that these changes would make druids equal to clerics ("anyway, good luck with the new abilities, and don't forget to invis <EM><STRONG>your fellow clerics</STRONG></EM>.")&nbsp;The people who praised him&nbsp;also must have missed his post saying that clerics were entitled to be upset over druid changes because clerics only got a bug fix.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mahzz</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Or some of us were being mildly sarcastic in our thanks.</DIV>	
