		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>to Mahzz, bluetiger and rubiensandwhich</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think I could probably work with you guys if it ever came to mutually balancing the classes.&nbsp;&nbsp; bluetiger and I have disagreed a lot--mainly on him not thinking that clerics need anything now--that they should wait til later---but we would see on that.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>let me first point out one thing here.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I as a cleric left your board for over a week when asked and even when posting here now, my post come about once for every 10 post.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; eqneedsbettertechs posts every other post--he has 20 post to my one on my own class board.&nbsp;&nbsp; trust me--no cleric here comes close to being like eqneedsbettertechs over there.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; he has totally trashed our board so it is not even usable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>second.&nbsp;&nbsp; I am not nor never have been against the druid healing.&nbsp;&nbsp; you can go back all the way to when we were doing the re-envisioning on eqdruids--that is where bluetiger and I clashed.&nbsp;&nbsp; You yourself bluetiger, know I never said druids should not get healing upgrades.&nbsp;&nbsp; I merely argued that clerics are not the perfect class you all think and pointed out what upgrades they need.&nbsp;&nbsp; you saying clerics were not entitled to them as a condition of druid healing ignored the fact that we were talking what each class needs--just like we are now.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; clerics need help in stacking and in offering a second role to group.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>to illustrate this let me point out an example (no not even soloing heh heh)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>a group of your friends are together exping or farming runes in an area they are having a blast in.&nbsp;&nbsp; You arrive with your druid and there is already a druid in group.&nbsp;&nbsp; No problem right--one of you heals and the other dps's without the group suffering at all.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>now if I arrive at that same group of friends and there is already a cleric there?&nbsp;&nbsp; sure they let me in because I am a friend---but dps and utility suffer.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>you need healing I agree.&nbsp;&nbsp; heck make there be 3 healing classes.&nbsp;&nbsp; but all three of those healing classes need to be able to fill a second slot.&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>ie shaman can heal or slow and shaman with panther on pets contribute at least 200 dps per pet--they can keep it on a couple pets easy is 400 dps.&nbsp; they dont fill tank role</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>druids can dps (you say not as well as a dps class--but your healing is not balanced against the best dps classes, it is balanced against us so your dps would be balanced against us)&nbsp; so you can fill healing or one of the 3 dps slots.&nbsp;&nbsp; you dont slow and you dont tank</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>clerics can fill one slot--healing.&nbsp;&nbsp; we used to be able to tank--now we dont last as long as a enchanter with runes.&nbsp;&nbsp; we dont slow.&nbsp;&nbsp; we dont dps.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>your arguements--</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1.&nbsp; well you dont need a slower just use two clerics to equal the slowing.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; well with shaman/druid healing getting closer to clerics---shaman could do this even better--two shaman healers and slow</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. move to harder zone and utilize the better healing---eventually you reach a point where if all of us can heal every zone=that higher zone needing two clerics healing is not there.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Also like I mentioned sometimes my friends are where they want to be and dont want to move.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. eqneedsbettertechs listed a list of things we can do&nbsp;&nbsp; LOL root to ghetto mez mobs--well with snare and your better roots you are better at that and almost everyone is.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>stuns---they are broke in high levels--ask any paladin</DIV>
<DIV>atone---mobs resist that like it was cast by level 1 character</DIV>
<DIV>ivu---would be about as useful as invis vs summonded mobs</DIV>
<DIV>go to places where there are undead?---yeah everyone lets head to estate of unrest, mistmoore or the two or three rare undead spots.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>you can argue against it all you want--but clerics are as broke as druids right now---just in different areas(druids in healing and clerics in dps/utility).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; you say we are guaranteed groups--we are not.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I see many clerics lfg and for hours.&nbsp;&nbsp; because if healing is covered they offer not one other thing to a group.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>as to why I am here on these boards---because our boards have become unusable thanks to eqneedsbettertechs.&nbsp;&nbsp; on a page with 12 post--8 will be his.&nbsp;&nbsp; I would happily go back to my board and post what we need to fix us--if I could without him.&nbsp;&nbsp; and for people here to say he brings up good points shows how little they realize about playing a cleric.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>go for your better healing and good luck.&nbsp;&nbsp; I do hope you get it, but dont think a clerics world is all roses.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I dont think you realize what all we do without.&nbsp;&nbsp; stackability is huge.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
