		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			"bluetiger and I have disagreed a lot--mainly on him not thinking that clerics need anything now--that they should wait til later---but we would see on that."<br><br>Not quite. I said that clerics getting changes is not a prerequisite to druids getting changes. When you say NO on druid changes UNLESS clerics get something in return... I wholeheartedly disagree with you.<br><br>If your position is that druids need changes, clerics do too, if you are happy druids are getting changes and hope that clerics will get changes soon... I would be in agreement with you. <br><br>And you know I never trashed clerics getting better at soloing. I did trash clerics getting better healing though...<br><br>"a group of your friends are together exping or farming runes in an area they are having a blast in.   You arrive with your druid and there is already a druid in group.  "<br><br>The problem with this scenario is that you assume that having a druid in group is common. While I agree with you on stackability, the druid need is even more basic : we are struggling to get in a group, period. <br><br>You can argue all you want that clerics are struggling to get groups... I know all clerics in my guild receive tells for group the minute they put LFG up for getting invited to the raid. Most are now anonymous to try and avoid the flow of tells they get. It's funny, but as a druid I never have that problem.<br><br>So you see, right now, druids getting in a group is our focus. We are not even at the point of considering getting 2 or more in a group...<br><br>"1.  well you dont need a slower just use two clerics to equal the slowing.    well with shaman/druid healing getting closer to clerics---shaman could do this even better--two shaman healers and slow"<br><br>The point is, clerics can fill that slot... AND stack with a second cleric.<br><br>"go to places where there are undead?"<br><br>There are actually a few high level zones with undead in them. Actually, even more so than animals. But yeah, there could be more of both. There are animals, they are just not flagged as animals...<br><br>"druids can dps (you say not as well as a dps class--but your healing is not balanced against the best dps classes, it is balanced against us so your dps would be balanced against us)"<br><br>Again... a druid healing does not have the luxury of DPS, unless the zone is trivial. He needs med breaks to sustain a reasonable pull rate... how on earth can you say that this druid does DPS on top of that? Yes, we can DPS (some, evidently, many classes are better at it, or SoE would not have seen a need to provide an option to increase it by a whole 25%), but we cannot do it *at the same time* as healing. We neither have the spells, nor the mana for that.<br><br>So YES, a druid doing DPS fills a "DPS" slot. Thus, it's looked at against other DPS classes. Groups say "hmmm, if i take druid, I get some but not great DPS, and a safety net in healing that wont help kill rate, but *may* help us if poo hits the fan... Is that worth it?" Unless the rest of the group is not setup decently, the usual answer is No, let's get another class.<br><br>The change SoE is proposing will change that equation, hopefully enough, but we will see. <br><br>Brum, again, when you stop trying to link cleric changes to druid changes, we will be more in agreement.<br><br>Bluetiger	
