		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>"<EM>I think I could probably work with you guys if it ever came to mutually balancing the classes.</EM>&nbsp;" -brum</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>No you couldn't, because&nbsp;you insist on holding druid fixes hostage to cleric fixes. You refuse to accept the very basic premise that&nbsp;the druid's shortcomings in healing power is causing a severe lack of group desirability -- and since this is primarily a grouping game (increasinly moreso with each expansion release), that issue needs to be addressed regardless of what is done for other classes. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"<EM>let me first point out one thing here.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I as a cleric left your board for over a week when asked and even when posting here now, my post come about once for every 10 post.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; eqneedsbettertechs posts every other post--he has 20 post to my one on my own class board</EM>." -brum</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That is irrelevent. You're basically saying that two wrongs make a right.&nbsp;A druid is interfering with discussions on&nbsp;the cleric&nbsp;board, so that makes it okay for&nbsp;you to&nbsp;do the same&nbsp;here? </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But frankly, that's just an excuse.&nbsp;You did the same thing&nbsp;on The Druids Grove, back when Sobe opened a "priest balance" forum and provided separate boards for each of the three priest classes. You, Hurk, and a few other clerics had more posts in the druid section than ANY of the druids there except one of the moderators. Meanwhile, there were barely any posts from druids on the cleric or shaman boards. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So let's just drop the whole "eqneedsbettertechs is trashing the cleric board" rationalization. You&nbsp; have never needed an&nbsp;excuse to derail druid threads and interfere with our discussions by inserting your own agendas.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;"<EM>a group of your friends are together exping or farming runes in an area they are having a blast in.&nbsp;&nbsp; You arrive with your druid and there is already a druid in group.&nbsp;&nbsp; No problem right--one of you heals and the other dps's without the group suffering at all</EM>." -brum</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Got news for ya. If they have a druid as main healer, they are definitely already tying up another slot with a slower, and they have less room for flexibility if they want to be productive.&nbsp;They would&nbsp;only invite another druid if&nbsp;it's a friend (same reason they'd invite a second cleric in your example). If it's not a friend, I can almost guarantee that&nbsp;second druid is going to be turned down in favor of a *real* DPS class. &nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In more challenging content, they'd invite a second druid because they're not comfortable with a single druid as main healer and they cannot find a cleric. You can say "oh look those druids stack in a group" -- but think of the reason *why* they stack:&nbsp; it takes two of them to fill one role.&nbsp; If that's what you want for clerics, start asking for nerfs because you'll need to lose a lot of healing power before you'll have to sacrifice a DPS slot for a second healer. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As for your other comments, I've read them all before, and we're still waiting for you to see past the end of your nose long enough to read the legitimate answers you have been given on each and every point. If you want to rehash&nbsp;it all&nbsp;yet again, I really believe the space would be more appropriately wasted on the CLERIC board. You know, the place for CLERIC issues? Did you forget which class THIS board was created for?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Not trying to sound rude, but seriously... you're being a hypocrit when you complain about 'eqneedsbettertechs' and then proceed to do the same thing he's doing. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Regards,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mahzz</DIV>	
