gimliie wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
rubiensandwhich wrote:
<DIV>Now on to the problems clerics are having, I truly hope that clerics get invis although i can do a quick search and find at least 5 items that are cleric useable with clicky invis.</DIV>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>You one of the few druids whos post i actualy want to take the time to read. I just dont agree with this statement though. There is the VT mask sadly though going back and raiding VT just to get me this mask is simply not an option. Then there is the current Fabled BP that will be gone outa game in about a month is pretty much perma camped. If there are other items that have invis without charges that are resonbly obtainable I would love to know what they are. </FONT><BR>
<HR>

<P></P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>I really hope that the changes for druids go threw it is not balance that only 1 class can be healer. I also really hope some of the long standing things about the cleric class that are just ment to be annoying are removed but they will not be. </FONT></DIV>
<P><BR>
<HR>
</P>
<P>Sadly the other items I know of do have charges, and Im sorry you cant get back to vt, its one of my all time favorite zones in the game, although it can be a pita. The point that I was trying to make, was while I cant think of any logical reason to not give clerics invis, and I would be first in line to help them get that, there are options and its not a gamebreaking thing where some group is going to send you a tell and ask you "do you have invis", or even better, a group isnt going to break up becuase you cant invis. Sadly that happens alot to druids.</P>
<P><BR>&nbsp;</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
brum wrote:<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>eqneedsbettertechs posts every other post--he has 20 post to my one on my own class board.&nbsp;&nbsp; trust me--no cleric here comes close to being like eqneedsbettertechs over there.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; he has totally trashed our board so it is not even usable.</DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><BR>This was actually covered in my posts directed at you, but let me be more concise. I want to see a magelo before I believe that he has ever played a druid in the end game ( by that I mean post 65 in post pop zones). The things he writes about druids just arent doable, either that or he is way more uber skilled and better geared&nbsp; than I am. Click on the link to his name and pull up find all posts by this user and you will see he has never posted anything on these boards, but he has posted on the serker, rogue and cleric boards, I think he just likes to stir the pott and talk out the side of his neck but hey who am I to judge.</P>
<P>Let me give ya a scenerio,</P>
<P>1.&nbsp;right now its fairly easy to box/pl a cleric up to 60-65. Now some peeps are going to do this anyways but for the sake of argument just follow me here.</P>
<P>2. The druid class is getting scarcer and scarcer, how do I know this, I grew up with most of the druids on my server (gamewise), wwe al solo'd in the same areas so I know most of the druids that play on terris. Now those zones are empty and alot of those names arent on anymore except to raid.</P>
<P>3. druids have a hard time healing in the high end content which mens that if people want to do groups they have to wait for a cleric to log on and want to xp in that zone. </P>
<P>Now I believe (I could be wrong), that you are under the impression that if we get beefed up we will take groups from you, which is a false assumption, Those groups are going to form with or without a cleric eventually. What I see happening now is that a clerics main competition is that its faster and easier to make a cleric bot, than to have to wait for a cleric all the time. And if healing stayys out of balance more and more of your compettion is going to be from bots and live clerics wont be needed. Now if ya think this cant happen you may want to take alook around you, its happening already. Go to rss, mpg and the back side of rcod and look at the amount of groups that are camping with bots. The way we make that kind of competition go away is to open up the zone to more people, which means that we need more healer capable of healing in those zones. Currently the only toons capable are clerics and there is not enough clerics for all the groups to form, refer back to point 1.</P>
