<P>3.<BR></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
rubiensandwhich wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>

<P>Now I believe (I could be wrong), that you are under the impression that if we get beefed up we will take groups from you, which is a false assumption, Those groups are going to form with or without a cleric eventually. What I see happening now is that a clerics main competition is that its faster and easier to make a cleric bot, than to have to wait for a cleric all the time. And if healing stayys out of balance more and more of your compettion is going to be from bots and live clerics wont be needed. Now if ya think this cant happen you may want to take alook around you, its happening already. Go to rss, mpg and the back side of rcod and look at the amount of groups that are camping with bots. The way we make that kind of competition go away is to open up the zone to more people, which means that we need more healer capable of healing in those zones. Currently the only toons capable are clerics and there is not enough clerics for all the groups to form, refer back to point 1.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>and there is not a thing being added to clerics to make anyone take an active cleric over a botted one.&nbsp;&nbsp; that is my point exactly.&nbsp;&nbsp; I have no problems with you getting healing.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I want some of the other abililties ie dps and utiliity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; something besides healing I would be doing that the botted cleric couldnt.&nbsp; ask yourself just how little clerics do offer besides healing if they are using bots to do the same job active clerics do?&nbsp;&nbsp; my points are--welcome to more healing spots.&nbsp;&nbsp; I dont care if I share the healing with you---I want (and as an active cleric as you point out above need) something to establish me as something other then just a heal bot.&nbsp;&nbsp; I want stackability and something I am actively participating in a group in such as meaningful dps and utility.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>otherwise the three types of healers you will see after the changes are</P>
<P>druids</P>
<P>shaman</P>
<P>and BOTTED clerics--cause why bring an active cleric when they dont do anything but heal anyhow? </P>
<P>so yeah the active clerics would be the ones losing the slots---the botted ones wouldnt.</P>
<P>anyhow--good luck with your healing upgrades and have fun in game<BR></P>
