<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3721#M3721">188</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 647 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Having played a Druid since beta I see the same thing over and over and over.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Every time the game changes (new expansions) with harder mobs that hit faster, have more hpts, AC and are immune to more things Druids come to SOE and ask for an increase in healing or other help. After the long hard fight for our incompete heal (which was supposed to be a 75% Complete Heal but without a cap - thanks clerics for the cap!) the clerics moaned that they would no longer be needed in group because of everything Druids can do. This was two years ago.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And everytime Druids got something clerics had to be compensated in some way. Well I'm sick and tired of this!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What compensation have Druids EVER gotten when we were nerfed or had our abilities distributed to all the other classes? Well clerics? Do you think runspeed and ports were not as integral a part of the druid class as your precious res and level 39 complete heals which to this day take less mana and heal more than even a level 70 druid.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Here is an easy test for everyone.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Do a LFG and see how many clerics cannot get a group. Now do it for druids? Not hard to see what classes are wanted or needed in todays game. If not for the shortage of clerics even more druids would be looking.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It is possible that maybe, just maybe clerics do not need "major" changes as they are so desired a class?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Why don't you (clerics) wait and see if these proposed changes actually hurt your class in any way before you try and keep the druid class in the dirt where it has been for so many years now. Now that's a novel thought isn't it? You cried wolf when we got the incomplete heal and druids still could not get a group while you have no problems. Why should we believe you this time? When we got that incomplete heal it was supposed to spell the end of the cleric class. Has it? Have druids taken ove rin the past two years? In fact, due to the game changing even more, we are worse off.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SOE already stated that all classes will be given limited solo abiltiies so please get off our back! It's taken years to get SOE's attention for helping the druid class - why must you continue to kick us when we are down? Just to keep us down? The Druid Class is a beaten hollow shell of it's former self. For the sake of the few of us who still play the class why does it upset you so that we might be getting something for our class after all these years?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I have never went on the clerics boards and tried to get things taken away from them or keep you from getting things your class may need. Why do this to us?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As long as clerics have res we could have the exact same spell set and groups would still prefer clerics over druids. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Or are you just enjoying the debate like many do not caring what damage you may be causing others?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-Cass</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							March 2005<br><br>Druids are a unique challenge in that the class is divided evenly between you offensive druids who enjoy doing damage, and you defensive druids who prefer to play the role of healer. We want to support both play styles, but if we were to increase both halves of the druid equally the class would quickly become overpowered. Our plan is to introduce a new option where a druid can enter into a particular “mode” or “stance” where they become better at one part at the expense of the other. Our preferred solution for this is to add an innate ability for druids. The ability would get its own button similar to abilities such as backstab or track. You will be able to be in one of three states and can switch between them once every 5 minutes.<br
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
