<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&message.id=3726#M3726">193</a> of 780
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 632 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Putting my discussion of dps and number crunching&nbsp;on hold for now since people only read the part of my posts that makes em angry (for instance I mentioned pets as dps like 4 times and clearly stated outnuke isnt outdps).&nbsp; So much for being positive.<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Blayze_Meduenin wrote:<BR>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>The problem is if druids can adequately heal all content (which you are arguiing for in this post) where does that leave&nbsp; clerics?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>When a druid can heal as well as a cleric but also has more utility it puts the cleric as 2nd choice for healer, in other words they are 2nd best at their ONLY role.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>That is why clerics need more utiity as druids need more healing. Cleric extra utility/dps is not 'being used to hold ruid healing hostage' as many put it, but the balance needs of the two are interwoven.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>In every zone a druid can heal they are the first choice of healer because being able to heal more versus adding more utility beyond that point is all that matters.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>An increase in druid healing narrows the field where a cleric is first choice for healer even more (and if a druid is able to heal in all content as the quoted poster above wants that means cleric becomes the 2nd best healer by virtue of this). That is why any increase in druid healing must be BALANCED by an increase in cleric utility and/or dps.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>A cleric, offering only healing yet being the 2nd choice at that role because a druid can do the job as well and offer all their utility as extras is ridiculous.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>I dont mind druids getting healing upgrades, but you have to be reasonable and see why those upgrades need to be balanced with cleric upgrades to their weak areas as well.</FONT></DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Healing: There's really three levels of healing, not the can and can't mentioned alot: (1) Can't heal (or can heal but with big med breaks), (2) can heal but can do nothing else, and (3) can heal with mana to spare.&nbsp; When a druid can't heal, they can't heal, and no one will want them for heals.&nbsp; When a druid can heal but can do nothing else, they are the second choice because a cleric can heal and dps a little on the side (fitting in a nuke in between chs might be really hard, but nuking a running mob or a mob about to run should be fair game).&nbsp; When a druid can heal with mana to spare, they are superior to a cleric assuming that they have enough spare mana to do something useful.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Clerics have the edge on healing in case 1&nbsp;because the difference between a cleric and druid healer is frequently the difference between wos and mpg, for example.&nbsp; Better healing can lead to inherently better xp/loot due to a better zone.&nbsp; Clerics have a superior ch, hots, that odd rune spell (pov), and better buffs to make this possible.&nbsp; Rez is nice but not really necessary; one person can be rezzed just as well by a druid and snaring a passing cleric will get the xp later on (aa rez preserves some mana too, which I appreciate as a bard).&nbsp; Mass rezzing is the cleric's domain, but exodus is cooler than mass rezzing imo, assuming the druid doesn't die first.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Clerics also have the edge on healing in case 2 because dps &gt; no dps and cleric buffs are superior (unless you need the mana regen on steeloak in rare cases).&nbsp; Getting enough mana to cast ds helps some, but a cleric is still preferred.&nbsp; This is the situation where&nbsp;many druids might heal in endgame content; it's possible, but less efficient than a cleric.&nbsp; When a druid has no mana they have no utility, which moots the whole druid = cleric + utility point.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Druids have the edge in case 3 in certain cases.&nbsp; The thing about new healing mode is that nukes are very weak, and so a cleric would still be better dps if the druid is nuking on the side in heal mode.&nbsp; The utility part comes in here though, and a druid that casts ds and snares every mob could be considered just as good as a cleric.&nbsp; Snaring would save a ranger snare for example, which is essentially the same as nuking at a ranger level damage/mana ratio (better than the healing mode penalty, but still not great).&nbsp; When a druid has mana to spare in normal mode, they tend to be better than clerics, so a druid healer is better when farming and such.&nbsp; However, most people want to go to a better zone instead of using a druid in their most efficient mode.&nbsp; A druid might be better than a cleric&nbsp;healing a 35% shielding 15k tank in rs, but that's an extremely rare case.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So in most cases, a cleric is still considered better than a druid.&nbsp; Arguing that an increase in druid healing must be balanced is rather silly because the balance is inherent in the increase: druids can heal more but they lose their dps advantage over the cleric.&nbsp; Also, there's no reason to REQUIRE some counterbalancing; if druid heals were half what they were now there'd be no reason to give clerics a bonus if they fixed druid healing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>One thing about anecdotal comparisons about healing and such: they don't really resolve the issue.&nbsp; If you have a 7.5k buffed tank in wos you're going to be hurting no matter what class you use to heal.&nbsp; I doubt that was the case, but unless there's a controlled comparison (cleric was healing while&nbsp;I dpsed, then cleric left, a druid came in and took over heals) it's rather meaningless.&nbsp; I can heal better than a level 10 cleric with manasong, dps, and take no med breaks at the same time, but that doesn't make me a better healer than a cleric.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
