		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Blayze_Meduenin wrote:<BR>
<DIV>
<DIV>brum - I think you are completely missing&nbsp; the point here. We aren't arguing about a druids ability to farm runes or to heal in low or moderate challenging content. We are arguing the fact that druids cant heal in RSS, MPG or the hgher level DoN missions. The top 1% of uber druids might have a shot of it but the rest of us decently clad and 100ish aa druids can't do it properly.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Example is this. In WoS F2 two nights ago I was grouped with another druid, me 67, 100 aa's&nbsp;with some tier 1 OOW&nbsp;armour and DoN augments, 5650 mana and FT 12. The other druid 68 with whatever he had, certainly had all teh healing aa's. With me main healing and him patch healing we still struggled to keep the group hunting without having to take med breaks. If their hadn't been 2 of us healing with the occasional help of group heals from a shmmy, the group would have wiped or semi wiped in loads of occasions.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thats totally unexceptable in my books. It takes 2 decent druids nad some help from a shammy to replace a single healing class fro a group to hunt effectively. Just before you or any other clerics dive in here, both of us knew what we were doing. I've played my druid as a main healer most of his career.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I don't mind clerics posting on this board but please don't whime about the cleric class and try to keep your examples relevant. Talking about how its ok to have two druids in a group farming runes has nothing to do with why SoE sees the need to raise a druids healing ability. It's because they can't heal in the end game effectively.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>The problem is if druids can adequately heal all content (which you are arguiing for in this post) where does that leave&nbsp; clerics?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>When a druid can heal as well as a cleric but also has more utility it puts the cleric as 2nd choice for healer, in other words they are 2nd best at their ONLY role.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>That is why clerics need more utiity as druids need more healing. Cleric extra utility/dps is not 'being used to hold ruid healing hostage' as many put it, but the balance needs of the two are interwoven.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>In every zone a druid can heal they are the first choice of healer because being able to heal more versus adding more utility beyond that point is all that matters.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>An increase in druid healing narrows the field where a cleric is first choice for healer even more (and if a druid is able to heal in all content as the quoted poster above wants that means cleric becomes the 2nd best healer by virtue of this). That is why any increase in druid healing must be BALANCED by an increase in cleric utility and/or dps.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>A cleric, offering only healing yet being the 2nd choice at that role because a druid can do the job as well and offer all their utility as extras is ridiculous.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>I dont mind druids getting healing upgrades, but you have to be reasonable and see why those upgrades need to be balanced with cleric upgrades to their weak areas as well.</FONT></DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Fine.... clerics need some things. Go ask SOE for them. SOE wants there to be three healing classes - you have other issues so present them to SOE instead of trying to keep another class (a class already near death) down.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Have druids not already given up enough? What have clerics given up? anything? anything at all?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>-Cass<BR></P>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							March 2005<br><br>Druids are a unique challenge in that the class is divided evenly between you offensive druids who enjoy doing damage, and you defensive druids who prefer to play the role of healer. We want to support both play styles, but if we were to increase both halves of the druid equally the class would quickly become overpowered. Our plan is to introduce a new option where a druid can enter into a particular “mode” or “stance” where they become better at one part at the expense of the other. Our preferred solution for this is to add an innate ability for druids. The ability would get its own button similar to abilities such as backstab or track. You will be able to be in one of three states and can switch between them once every 5 minutes.<br
							</div>
								
