		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>How easy it is to get sidetracked....<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There's no point to arguing cleric/druid balancing in general.&nbsp;&nbsp; It's kind of moot for purposes of the class restructuring, and more particularly, for purposes of druid "mode" discussions.&nbsp;&nbsp; It's moot because SOE has stated the goal for defensive mode as druids being 80% of the effectiveness of a cleric in a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any questions of what clerics need belong on the cleric board, not here, and should not be tied to this&nbsp;80% determination. &nbsp;While I have always had great sympathy for the limited gameplay of clerics (and have not argued against any changes to make clerics more fun to play), the goal for now is to determine what 80% of the effectiveness of a cleric really means with regard to the primary healing role in a group.&nbsp;&nbsp; And with the help of several well-spoken clerics in this thread, I think we now have a fairly good handle on that.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I've submitted some specific questions to SOE on this topic, such as what does 80% effectiveness mean to them, and will SOE consider the lack of healing tools as part of the package.&nbsp; I'll let you know if I hear anything.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Scirocco<br>Druid Community Correspondent
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
