			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
gimliie wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Cassea-Eci wrote:
<P>Have druids not already given up enough? What have clerics given up? anything? anything at all?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>-Cass<BR></P>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>I generaly try to be positive on your boards. Anyone who has read my post should know that i am in favor of druids geting upped healing. But this, lol this has got to be the funniest statement i have ever seen made on the dev boards. Ok I'll be back off to my cleric board now to try and get a post in around the trash that is EQneeds or what ever the hell his name is. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>On a side note while i am not in favor of you guys geting an exp rez I do think it is a great idea to drop the req lvl for the call AA to lvl 66. I dont know what the cast time on the&nbsp;AA is atm. Is there one? Someone can enlighten me to this. At any rate I think it should have about 10sec cast time, the same as a cleric click, and have the reuse droped to like 30sec to a min. If soe expects you to heal in groups you need to be able to get your group back after deaths faster than 1 per 10min or whatever it is now. As for exp on the rez there is allways SC in the lobby, you got like what 2 hours after death to get exp rez? I dono im a cleric never payed attetion &gt;&lt;. You can group with a paladin, or a necro. As for necro rez before someone starts talkin about EE's I am fully in favor of dropeing the reg cost on their rez to a dot or normal emerald or hell a jasper somethinig to make it more useable. To me this would be a great change. You would have 3 tank classes 3 healing classes and 3 rezzing </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Also i really expect the 20% or is it 25% its late im out of it, bonus to your heals to include your CH. There just is no way that it would be worth it if its not. you got what 2 healing lines excludeing 1 of them would seem stupid. </FONT></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>I admit that I was a bit upset when I posted this. I normally post what I consider more normal posts with some thought but I guess some of the recent post by proclaimed clerics really got to me. Coming here and posting about what "may" happen as a reason to keep the druid class down is something clerics have done in the past and having "some" clerics proclaim that if you "give away" some cleric abilities it will hurt the cleric class just struck a nerve after everything that the druid class has already "given away."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The fact is that aside from druids (and to a lessor extent shamen) obtaining that incomplete heal, clerics have not had any of their abiltiies given away and even this was not all that bad as it was given to one (or two if you include shamen) class and not every class in the game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you give druids better healing then "possibly" clerics have "some" competition with druids for "some" healing spots but the other 14 classes still need these two classes for healing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now look at what happened when druids gave up runspeed (only two classes had) and ports (only two classes had) to "every" class in the game. Now while shamen also had SOW (bards but you had to be grouped with them to keep it) and wizards also port, only the druid clas had both of these and instead of giving these VERY important abilities to one or two other classes they gave them to all the classes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So instead of 14 other classes still needing ports and runspeed, no one needs these abilities. This was dine for "the good of the game" but it decimated the druid class - a class, mind you, that was already having issues obtaining groups even with near exclucivity of these abilities.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So yes claiming that if clerics were to "share" healing with two other healing classes it would destroy their class falls on deaf ears when you tell this to a class that has already been destroyed by having half of their abilities (runspeed and fast travel - ports) already given out to - not two others classes - but "the entire game!"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do wish clerics the very best, as I did two years ago when we got incomplete heal, in obtaining things their class needs but if you think helping one class means "automatic" compensation take a hard look at what druids obtained when half of our abilities (and the ONLY abilities we really did not share as other classes have heals and DPS) were given away to "everyone" and of course the answer is a big nothing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-Cass</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							March 2005<br><br>Druids are a unique challenge in that the class is divided evenly between you offensive druids who enjoy doing damage, and you defensive druids who prefer to play the role of healer. We want to support both play styles, but if we were to increase both halves of the druid equally the class would quickly become overpowered. Our plan is to introduce a new option where a druid can enter into a particular “mode” or “stance” where they become better at one part at the expense of the other. Our preferred solution for this is to add an innate ability for druids. The ability would get its own button similar to abilities such as backstab or track. You will be able to be in one of three states and can switch between them once every 5 minutes.<br
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-25-2005</span> <span class=time_text>05:59 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
				&nbsp;
				
